<HEAD>Youth Crushed While Looking For Fishing Weights</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Retransmits a0531 to fix cycle designator</NOTE>
<DATELINE>JONESVILLE, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A 16-year-old looking for fishing weights was crushed to death when he got too near a heavy steel counterweight at an oil well near his home, authorities said. <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Heath </PERSON> <PERSON> Goins </PERSON> and two friends were in a field between looking for pieces of metal to tie onto their fishing lines when the accident occurred Thursday, the Catahoula Parish sheriff's office said The friends told deputies that the 8-inch-thick, 12-inch-wide counterweight pinned <PERSON> Goins </PERSON> against an upright of the well. Oil wells that operate automatically are scattered throughout the area.
