<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The ships and crewmen attacked by <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> Saturday were ineligible for <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> distress assistance under the <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> administration's rules of engagement in the <LOCATION> Persian </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION>, a <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman said. `` The supertankers were inside one of the exclusion zones, which both belligerents have declared and they were servicing the port of a belligerent,'' spokeswoman <PERSON> Sondra </PERSON> <PERSON> McCarty </PERSON> said. `` Each of these factors disqualifies shipping from <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> distress assistance.'' <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> warships are now permitted to intervene on request in attacks on neutral shipping as well as to provide `` humanitarian aid'' to non-U.S. flagged vessels, but only in international waters. Today's attack occurred in Iranian waters, at the <LOCATION> Larak </LOCATION> oil depot, the latest target in <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION>'s intensified attempt to strangle petroleum exports that help <LOCATION> Tehran </LOCATION> finance the war. <PERSON> McCarty </PERSON> repeated <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> assertions that `` there can be no military solution the war,'' and that any fighting that prolongs the conflict is regrettable. She pleaded anew for <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Security </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> action to implement a 10-month old resolution calling for a truce in the conflict and an arms embargo against belligerents who fail to heed the cease-fire call. The <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> have declined to endorse the resolution, asserting that diplomatic efforts toward a truce have not been exhausted.
