 the <ORGANIZATION> Tigre </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Front </ORGANIZATION>. <LOCATION> Eritrea </LOCATION> and <PERSON> Tigre </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Ethiopia </LOCATION>'s northernmost provinces, are the worst hit by a drought that threatens the lives of 7 million people, nearly half of whom are in the war zone. Eritrean rebels have been fighting for 27 years in <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>'s longest civil war, and <PERSON> Tigrean </PERSON> rebels took up arms 14 years ago
