<DATELINE>PANAMA CITY, Panama (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Despite months of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> sanctions and a crumbling economy, Gen. <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> is hardening his position and preparing for months or possibly years more of confrontation with the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. A confident <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> on Friday sallied into the provinces, where he was cheered by peasants and hailed by small-town officials. Accompanied by several colonels in a show of military unity, <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION>'s defiant leader, accused in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> of drug trafficking, dismissed prospects for a negotiated settlement with the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>'s comments to journalists indicated he considers himself and <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> a test case of historical proportions and that he is determined to rise to the occasion and challenge <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> might. `` Everything fell apart,'' he said in <LOCATION> La </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Negrita </LOCATION>, 90 miles west of the capital, when asked about recent U.S-Panamanian talks aimed at resolving <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION>'s political crisis over <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>'s leadership. The <ORGANIZATION> Washington </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Post </ORGANIZATION>, citing unidentified sources, reported in its Sunday editions that negotiations were at a delicate stage and that administration officials believed a deal would be struck within a few days or the talks would collapse. The administration is offering to drop drug-trafficking charges against <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> if he relinquished office Aug. 12 and left the country, the newspaper said. In addition, the administration would continue to recognize ousted President <PERSON> Eric </PERSON> <PERSON> Arturo </PERSON> <PERSON> Delvalle </PERSON> but also would allow <PERSON> Solis </PERSON> <PERSON> Palm