<HEAD>Mecham Criminal Trial Begins Thursday</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: INSERTS 3 grafs after 7th graf ``Mecham, one'' to UPDATE with
Mecham and McCain reax to delegate selection. Picks up 8th graf pvs
``In the criminal.''</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By LAURIE ASSEO</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PHOENIX, Ariz. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Impeached former Gov. <PERSON> Evan </PERSON> <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON>, facing trial this week on charges of concealing a $ 350,000 campaign loan, proclaimed faith in his innocence but uncertainty about whether he will be acquitted. <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON> remained in the spotlight Saturday, attending his state party convention and narrowly winning a seat at the Republican National Convention. <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON>, who was removed from office April 4 by the <ORGANIZATION> Legislature </ORGANIZATION>, could be sentenced to up to 22 years in prison if found guilty on all six felony counts of perjury, willful concealment and filing false documents. His brother and 1986 campaign treasurer, <PERSON> Willard </PERSON> <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON>, will be tried on three similar counts. The legal woes did not stop delegates to the state Republican convention Saturday from picking <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON> to be one of the state's 33 delegates when the party convenes this summer in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Orleans </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON> finished 17th in the balloting for 18 at-large delegates after losing a bid for one of the delegate seats allocated by congressional district. <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON>, one of the 717 delegates to his state party convention, said before voting that he believed he had `` strong support'' from rank-and-file party workers. <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON> supports Vice President <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>, but <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> campaign officials said <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON> was not on their list of recommended delegates. Told the results by reporters, <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON> said `` Hurrah'' and thrust his right fist upward. `` Well, for not being on a slate, that's not too bad,'' he said, adding `` this was not a referendum on me.'' Sen. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> McCain </PERSON>, R-Ariz., placed 10th in the at-large balloting with 296 votes to <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON>'s 271, and said he would attend the convention despite earlier reluctance to serve in a delagation with <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON> `` Amazing,'' <PERSON> McCain </PERSON> said of the vote. `` I respect the decision of the convention. I have no other comment about it.'' In the criminal case, <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON> and his brother are accused of concealing a $ 350,000 campaign loan from <LOCATION> Tempe </LOCATION> developer <PERSON> Barry </PERSON> <PERSON> Wolfson </PERSON> by failing to report it on <PERSON> Evan </PERSON> <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON>'s personal or campaign financial statements. `` I have committed no crime,'' <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON>, 64, said in a telephone interview last week. `` I should be found innocent because I do n't feel myself guilty as far as I can see. However, <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON> shied away from predicting he will be exonerated by a <ORGANIZATION> Maricopa </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Superior </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> jury and indicated he still may be open to a plea agreement if it did n't involve pleading guilty to a felony, a condition that prosecutors have rejected previously. <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON>'s 15-month governorship was a stormy one, beginning with his cancellation of a Martin Luther King holiday for state workers and ending with his repeated claims that his political and legal problems were the result of a massive conspiracy. He was removed from office when the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> convicted him of trying to thwart an investigation into an alleged death threat and misusing $ 80,000 from a protocol fund by loaning it to his auto dealership. The <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> dismissed a charge stemming from the campaign loan after some senators argued that voting on it would prejudice <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON>'s criminal case. On Monday, attorneys were set to present oral arguments before the state <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZ