inside and outside the <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON> administration, including former top aide <PERSON> Donna </PERSON> <PERSON> Carlson </PERSON>. She was one of several co-signers of the <PERSON> Wolfson </PERSON> loan and later was the object of the alleged death threat that became the centerpiece of <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON>'s <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> impeachment conviction. The governor's successor, Democratic Gov. Rose Mofford, was subpoenaed by the defense to testify about her knowledge of the campaign finance reporting law. She herself is under investigation for omissions from her reports, which she recently corrected. If the trial begins as scheduled, jury selection will start with distribution of a questionnaire designed to ferret out people with obvious bias. For his part, defense attorney <PERSON> Scott </PERSON> said, `` I'm confident that he should be acquitted.'' But he added, `` I'm not confident that it will happen.''
