 Lured by the warm promise of <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>, the three remaining presidential candidates are being drawn into a month-long primary campaign that is as much a preview of the fall campaign as a final nomination battleground. <PERSON> Jesse </PERSON> <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON>, trailing for the Democratic nomination, and <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>, the front-runner, have already made initial forays into the state, as has <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>, whose Republican nomination is assured. Each has a little different goal in mind in the state that has been reliably Republican in 20 years of presidential elections, but may not be so this year.
