<HEAD>Oil Prices Edge Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Oil futures prices settled slightly higher to end the week with another slow trading day. On the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, contracts for June delivery of <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> Intermediate, the benchmark <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> grade of crude oil, closed Friday at $ 17.49 per 42-gallon barrel, up 1 cent from Thursday's close. Among refined products for June delivery, contracts for wholesale unleaded gasoline settled .42 cent higher at 52.34 cents per gallon, while wholesale heating oil rose .24 cent to 47.47 cents per gallon. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Azarow </PERSON>, an analyst at the <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hutton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> securities firm, said the session amounted to `` a total non-event.'' `` Volume was down,'' he said, mainly because of a lack of any news able to move prices one way or the other. Also restricting volume, <PERSON> Azarow </PERSON> said, was a reluctance by some traders to trade too heavily before the upcoming meeting of oil ministers from the <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exporting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Countries </ORGANIZATION>, beginning June 8 in <LOCATION> Vienna </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Austria </LOCATION>. At the meeting, the <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> ministers are expected to try to find a way to restrict production in order to drive prices higher.
</TEXT>
